reviewText: 1 Explanation of the fundamental elements in Rasa is necessary to add to the course, for example, what is the definition of domain, entity, story in Rasa system. 2 Source code should be provided after the course completed.3 How to setup the Rasa environment is also required since the topic of this course is "First Chatbot" that cannot assume targeted students are already familiar with the Rasa environment.

The course is very well-explained and is not at all difficult to follow up with. It grants us live instruction videos and a cloud computer side by side at rhyme.com (Third Party Tool). The project mainly focuses on Rasa which is an AI powered ChatBot tool, and the Rasa ChatBot works with Python (.py) and Markdown (.md) files. My only complaint with it was that rhyme.com required a much stable and high speed internet in order to be able to stay connected with the Remote Desktop and expect quicker responses with it, and hopefully it will be looked after quite soon. The Guided Project gives a good amount of insights into using and configuring Rasa template. However, if it would have also included a video at starting (maybe as optional one) on how to install or setup Rasa, it would have been a plus.
